  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RPI_pwmMode</refname>
    <refpurpose>Function to set the mode for the PWM generator</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   RPI_pwmMode(mode)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>mode:</term>
      <listitem><para> The mode to set for the PWM generator. 'ms' (for mark:space) or 'bal' (for balanced)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function sets the mode for the PWM generator. The PWM generator can run in 2 modes – “balanced” and “mark:space”. The mark:space mode is traditional, however the default mode in the Pi is “balanced”. Switch modes by supplying the parameter: bal or ms
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
RPI_pwmMode('bal')
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

